-- Chinese Policy Banks Lend $165 Million to Mozambique, News Agency Reports
-- Fred Katerere
-- 2010-06-20T08:13:52Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-20/chinese-policy-banks-lend-165-million-to-mozambique-news-agency-reports.html

          
          
             Two Chinese banks agreed to finance
three projects in Mozambique totaling $165 million, Agencia de
Informacao de Mocambique reported today, citing Mozambican Prime
Minister  Aires Ali .  
 Of the amount, $65 million will be disbursed by the Export -
Import Bank of China , the Maputo-based state-run news agency
reported Ali as saying yesterday. Ali is on a five-day official
visit to China.  
 The Chinese Bank for Development will provide $80 million
for the construction of a new cement plant in the central
province of Sofala, with capacity to produce 500,000 metric tons
per year. It will also grant $20 million to finance a cotton-
processing plant in Magude, in the southern province of Maputo.  
